cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference LocalGhost in academic or published work, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
title: "LocalGhost"
abstract: >-
  LocalGhost is a local-first, privacy-focused AI platform built on cypherpunk
  principles. All inference and data storage runs on user-owned hardware with
  no cloud dependency. Fully open-source. The architecture consists of a fleet
  of daemons that each handle one function, currently starting at ten
  (ghost.noted for text ingest, ghost.framed for image ingest, ghost.voiced
  for audio ingest, ghost.tallyd for structured data ingest, ghost.synthd for
  the memory layer, ghost.cued for situational retrieval, ghost.mistd for
  peer-to-peer backup, ghost.shadowd as the adversarial sibling that
  challenges rather than confirms, ghost.secd for encryption and the
  multi-PIN duress model, and ghost.watchd for system health). The fleet is
  designed to grow as new modalities and jobs are added. The project
  includes a hidden-volume and duress-PIN security model designed to protect
  against compelled access, and a planned peer-to-peer backup layer
  (The Mist) using Reed-Solomon erasure coding over a Kademlia-style DHT.
  The project is currently in Phase 1 (architecture documented, daemon
  READMEs published, implementation in progress).
