    authors:
      - family-names: Cealicu
        given-names: Vlad
    year: 2026
    month: 3
    url: "https://www.localghost.ai/hard-truths/one-bad-quarter"
  - type: article
    title: "How to Prevent Building Your Own Dictator Brain"
    authors:
      - family-names: Cealicu
        given-names: Vlad
    year: 2026
    month: 4
    url: "https://www.localghost.ai/hard-truths/dictator-brain"
    notes: "Describes the architectural rationale for ghost.shadowd, a structurally separate daemon that builds a parallel identity oriented to challenge rather than confirm, running alongside the rest of the fleet."
  - type: article
    title: "The Model Trap"
    authors:
      - family-names: Cealicu
        given-names: Vlad
    year: 2026
    month: 4
    url: "https://www.localghost.ai/hard-truths/model-trap"
    notes: "Describes the two-layer behavioural test suite approach to surviving foundation model deprecation, with standardised benchmarks per daemon and a user-specific personal evaluation layer."
  - type: article
    title: "The Honeypot Under Your Desk"
    authors:
      - family-names: Cealicu
        given-names: Vlad
    year: 2026
    month: 4
    url: "https://www.localghost.ai/hard-truths/honeypot"
    notes: "Describes the threat model for ghost.secd, including the multi-PIN architecture, hidden-volume design, duress mode, and the purge function. Also covers the limits of the v1 threat model against targeted state-level adversaries."
  - type: article
    title: "How to Build a Critic Worth Listening To"
    authors:
      - family-names: Cealicu
        given-names: Vlad
    year: 2026
    month: 4
    url: "https://www.localghost.ai/hard-truths/critic-worth-listening-to"
    notes: "Follow-up to the dictator-brain post, arguing that ghost.shadowd should ask questions rather than give instructions, with an audit trail commitment to guard against hidden-chain manipulation."
  - type: article
    title: "How Memory Gets Made"
    authors:
      - family-names: Cealicu
        given-names: Vlad
    year: 2026
    month: 4
    url: "https://www.localghost.ai/hard-truths/how-memory-gets-made"
    notes: "Describes the cognitive-science grounding for the memory layer in ghost.synthd, including schema theory, encoding specificity, consolidation, and the user-in-the-loop calcification model."
  - type: article
    title: "The Bureaucracy Trap"
    authors:
      - family-names: Cealicu
        given-names: Vlad
    year: 2026
    month: 4
    url: "https://www.localghost.ai/hard-truths/the-bureaucracy-trap"
  - type: article
    title: "Before You Ask"
    authors:
      - family-names: Cealicu
        given-names: Vlad
    year: 2026
    month: 4
    url: "https://www.localghost.ai/hard-truths/before-you-ask"
    notes: "Describes the four-mechanism model (contextual remapping, priming, threshold, learning curve) behind ghost.cued, the daemon that surfaces memory from environmental context rather than explicit queries. Also discusses the structural limits of RAG at personal-memory scale."
  - type: article
    title: "The Ghost Has to Be Useful on Day One"
    authors:
      - family-names: Cealicu
        given-names: Vlad
    year: 2026
    month: 4
    url: "https://www.localghost.ai/hard-truths/day-one"
    notes: "Argues against onboarding questionnaires and personality tests in favour of inference from behavioural traces on the user's existing devices, with references to Kosinski/Youyou/Stillwell and the digital phenotyping literature."
